claims:
Claims 1. A big data analytics system comprising: an event monitoring controller configured to detect at least one user targeted event from an initial query data flow; an event conversion controller in signal communication with the event monitoring controller, and configured to determine at least one contextual element associated with the at least one user targeted event, and to automatically convert the at least one contextual element into a search criteria; an external data query builder controller configured to automatically execute an external search query based on the search criteria; and a data fusing controller configured to automatically fuse the at least one contextual element generated from the at least one user targeted event, together with external search results generated from the external search query and the initial query data flow to generate a fused data file. 2. The big data analytics system of claim 1 , wherein the event conversion controller automatically converts the at least one contextual element in response to generating an ontological hierarchy based on the at least one contextual element. 3. The big data analytics system of claim 2, wherein the ontological hierarchy includes information properties selected from a group comprising topics, context, and themes. 4. The big data analytics system of claim 3, wherein the information properties further includes individuals, classes, attributes, and relations based on the query data flow. 5. The big data analytics system of claim 4, wherein the information properties further comprises time period information and location information based on the query data flow. 6. The big data analytics system of claim 5, further comprising: a query data controller in signal communication with the event monitoring controller , the query data controller configured to retrieve the query data flow in response to a data request input by a user; a target event storage unit in signal communication with the event monitoring controller to store at least one user-defined targeted event input by the user; an ontology controller in signal communication with the event conversion controller, the ontology controller configured to determine at least one ontological individual based on the at least one contextual element; an external data system in signal communication with the external data query builder controller to generate the external search results based on the external search query, and to deliver the external search results to the data fusing controller; and 

 a visualization rendering controller in signal communication with the data fusing controller, the visualization rendering controller configured to generate a graphical user interface (GUI) that displays visual results of the fused data file. 7. The big data analytics system of claim 6, wherein the ontology controller determines at least one informational topic based on the at least one ontological individual and generates an expanded topic list including at least one individual synonym. 8. The big data analytics system of claim 7, wherein the ontology controller determines a class of the at least one ontological individual, and determines at least one property of the class. 9. The big data analytics system of claim 8, wherein the ontology controller determines a context corresponding to each topic based on a class corresponding to the ontological individual, and generates an expanded context list including at least one class synonym based on the determined context. 10. The big data analytics system of claim 9, wherein the ontology controller determines at least one attribute of the at least one property, and generates a second expanded list including at least one property synonym for each determined attribute of the at least one property. 11. A method of automatically generating a fused data file based on an initial query data flow obtained by a big data analytics system, the method comprising: detecting, via an electronic event monitoring controller, at least one user targeted event from the query data flow; determining, via an electronic event conversion controller, at least one contextual element associated with the at least one user targeted event; automatically converting, via the event conversion controller, the at least one contextual element into a search criteria; automatically executing, via an electronic external data query builder controller, an external search query based on the search criteria; and automatically fusing, via an electronic data fusing controller, the at least one contextual element generated from the at least one user targeted event, together with external search results generated from the external search query and the initial query data flow to generate the fused data file. 12. The method of claim 11, further comprising automatically converting, via the event conversion controller, the at least one contextual element in response to generating an ontological hierarchy based on the at least one contextual element. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein generating the ontological hierarchy further comprises generating an information property selected from a group comprising topics, context, and themes. 14. The method of claim 13, wherein generating the information properties further comprises generating expanded information selected from a group comprising individuals, classes, attribute, relations, time period, and location. 15. The method of claim 14, further comprising: retrieving, via an electronic query data controller, the query data flow in response to a data request input by a user; storing, via a target event storage unit, at least one user-defined targeted event input by the user; determining, via an electronic ontology controller, at least one ontological individual based on the at least one contextual element; generating, via an electronic external data system, the external search results based on the external search query, and delivering the external search results to the data fusing controller; and generating, via an electronic visualization rendering controller, a dashboard that correlates the at least one contextual element with the external search results; and generating a graphical user interface (GUI) that displays dashboard. 16. The method of claim 15, further comprising determining, via the ontology controller, at least one informational topic based on the at least one ontological individual. 17. The method of claim 16, further comprising determining, via the ontology controller, a class of the at least one ontological individual, and at least one property of the class. 18. A computer program product for automatically generating a fused data file based on an initial query data flow obtained by a big data analytics system, said computer program product comprising: a computer readable storage medium having stored thereon program instructions that are executable by at least one electronic hardware controller, the program instructions including: first program instructions executable by an electronic event monitoring controller to cause the event monitoring controller to detect at least one user targeted event from the query data flow; second program instructions executable by an event conversion controller, in signal communication with the event monitoring controller, to cause the conversion controller to determine at least one contextual element associated with the at least one user targeted event, and to automatically convert the at least one contextual element into a search criteria; 

 third program instructions executable by an electronic external data query builder controller to cause the external data query builder controller to automatically execute an external search query based on the search criteria; and fourth program instructions executable by an electronic data fusing controller to cause the data fusing controller to automatically fuse the at least one contextual element generated from the at least one user targeted event, together with external search results generated from the external search query and the initial query data flow to generate a fused data file. 19. The computer program product of claim 18, wherein the event conversion controller automatically converts the at least one contextual element in response to generating an ontological hierarchy based on the at least one contextual element. 20. The computer program product of claim 19, wherein the ontological hierarchy includes information properties selected from a group comprising topics, context, and themes. 21. The computer program product of claim 20, wherein the information properties further includes individuals, classes, attribute, relations, time period information, and location information. 22. A data analysis system comprising: an event monitoring controller configured to detect at least one user targeted event from an initial query data flow; an event conversion controller in signal communication with the event monitoring controller, and configured to automatically convert at least one contextual element associated with a detected user targeted event into a search criteria; a data fusing controller configured to automatically fuse the at least one contextual element generated from the at least one user targeted event, together with external search results generated from an external search query and the initial query data flow to generate a fused data file; and a graphic user interface (GUI) configured to display visual results of the fused data file. 23. The data analysis system of claim 22, wherein the event conversion controller automatically converts the at least one contextual element in response to generating an ontological hierarchy based on the at least one contextual element. 24. A method of automatically generating a fused data file based on an initial query data flow, the method comprising: detecting at least one user targeted event from the query data flow; 

 automatically converting at least one contextual element associated with a detected user targeted event into a search criteria; automatically fusing the at least one contextual element generated from the at least one user targeted event, together with external search results generated from an external search query and the initial query data flow to generate a fused data file; and displaying via a graphic user interface (GUI), visual results of the fused data file. 25. The method of claim 24, wherein converting the at least one contextual element comprises: determining an ontological hierarchy based on the at least one contextual element; and automatically generating the search criteria based on the ontological hierarchy.
